1.title: The Disastrous Life of a Psychic: Part 1

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Kusuo Saiki is a psychic with all sorts of supernatural powers. All he wants to do is to keep his head down and not draw attention to himself, but often things don't go as Kusuo hopes.

2.title: The Disastrous Life of a Psychic: Part 2

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: Although Kusuo's parents are currently fighting each other, he tries to stay out of it since he thinks that it is a problem that they need to work out for themselves.

3.title: The Worst of the Worst?! Riki Nendou

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: Kusuo's telepathic abilities allow him to read the thoughts of everyone around him. Everyone, that is, except for one particular individual.

4.title: Shun Kaidou, AKA The Jet-Black Wings

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

4.plot: Shun Kaidou is another one of Kusuo's classmates at PK Academy. He claims to have special powers and believes that there are dark forces at work that have evil plans for humanity.

5.title: Intelligent and Beautiful! Kokomi Teruhashi

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

5.plot: Kokomi Teruhashi is the quintessential pretty girl, leaving all the guys awestruck by her beauty and her sweet-as-honey personality. However, her attempt to bless Kusuo with her presence leads to some unexpected results.

6.title: Hot-Blooded! Dodgeball!: Part 1

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

6.plot: It's dodgeball time in Kusuo's PE class. As usual, Kusuo tries to conceal his abilities, but his attempts to keep a low profile lead to unexpected difficulties.

7.title: Hot-Blooded! Dodgeball!: Part 2

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

7.plot: Now that Kineshi is out of the game, Kusuo is the Paper Team's last hope to win. However, Kusuo is more concerned with figuring out how to keep his likability neutral so that he does not attract attention.

8.title: Reach Him! Sign of Love

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

8.plot: Yumehara Chiyo, one of Kusuo's classmates, has a crush on him. In order to get to know him better, she comes up with some plans to get closer to him.

9.title: Saiki Family Home Renovation?! Drastic Makeover!!

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

9.plot: Now that Kusuo's parents have reconciled, they want to sleep in the same bedroom. In order to do so, they need to move some furniture around and want Kusuo's help.

10.title: Deceive! Mind Control

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

10.plot: Have you ever wondered why none of the other students have called attention to Kusuo's unique looks? It all has to do with a little bit of mind control.

11.title: A Genius Magician?! Uryoku Chouno

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

11.plot: Saiki encounters a man performing a magic show in a park. Since he is a terrible magician, Saiki tries to get him to give up on pursuing this career. Also on the first day on school, Saiki and Kaidou follow Nendou to see why he's acting strange.

12.title: Second Encounter (on TV)! Uryoku Chouno

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

12.plot: Kusuo likes to watch TV because he can avoid reading the minds of the people on the TV, and thus is able to experience surprise and excitement like ordinary people. He experiences one such surprise when he sees Uryoku Chouno appear on TV.

13.title: How Shady! Dark Reunion!

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

13.plot: Shun is summoned by a mysterious individual who belongs to a group trying to destroy Dark Reunion. He says that they need Shun's help and tries to enlist Shun into the group.

14.title: Beachside Summer Story

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

14.plot: A new student, Aren Kuboyasu, has transferred to Saiki's class. Since he lived his entire life as a punk, he takes this opportunity to change himself and blend in with regular people. However, things don't go so smoothly for him.

15.title: A New School Term Starts! The Melancholy of Nendou

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

15.plot: On the first day of the new school term, Kusuo and Shun notice that Nendou is acting strange. Wanting to know what's up with him, they decide to follow him after school.

16.title: Please Make Me Your Apprentice!

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

16.plot: Saiki is approached by Toritsuka, another psychic who knows about Saiki's powers and who has the ability to see ghosts.

17.title: Psychic Medium in the Class Next Door

episode of.title: The Disastrous Life of Saiki K. (TV Series 2016– )

17.plot: Toritsuka enrolls in Saiki's school and uses his ghost-seeing ability to attract schoolgirls by telling them about their ghost guardians.
